Open SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS).
Right-click on "Databases" in the Object Explorer and select "Restore Database".
In the Restore Database window, select "Device" and click the "..." button on the right.
Choose "File" and locate the Staging.bak file in the appropriate directory.
Click "OK" to close the "Select backup devices" window.
Select "Staging" in the "To database" section and ensure that the path of the database file being restored is correct.
Click "OK" to start the database restore process. Wait until it completes.
